SIMPLE: obsidional
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Obsidional
<hw>Ob*sid"i*o*nal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>obsidionalis</ets>, from <ets>obsidio</ets> a siege,
<ets>obsidere</ets> to besiege: cf. F. <ets>obsidional</ets>. See
<er>Obsess</er>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to a siege.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Obsidional crown</b></col> <fld>(Rom. Antiq.)</fld>,
<cd>a crown bestowed upon a general who raised the siege of a
beleaguered place, or upon one who held out against a
siege.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Obsigillation</ent>⟦br⟧
